1
00:00:03,480 --> 00:00:08,680
The important reversals of our life, will come at any time without any warning.

2
00:00:08,680 --> 00:00:11,440
I'm... getting married.

3
00:00:11,440 --> 00:00:12,160
What?

4
00:00:12,160 --> 00:00:13,680
I'm sorry for taking Oppa from you.

5
00:00:13,680 --> 00:00:16,080
Bad jerk!

6
00:00:16,080 --> 00:00:20,900
I went to my ex-boyfriend's wedding to show a dignified image of myself.

7
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:23,700
Who knew that that would

8
00:00:23,700 --> 00:00:25,540
drive me into a corner even more?

9
00:00:25,540 --> 00:00:28,640
Do you know who Yoon Min Ji is?

10
00:00:28,640 --> 00:00:30,940
She's the president's wife's niece.

11
00:00:30,940 --> 00:00:32,620
I'm disappointed, Oh Ha Na.

12
00:00:32,620 --> 00:00:34,420
Oppa, was this the woman you were dating?

13
00:00:34,420 --> 00:00:36,940
Team Leader, what were you trying to pull at someone else's wedding?

14
00:00:36,940 --> 00:00:38,000
No wonder she get dumped.

15
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,360
You were dumped good, Oh Ha Na.

16
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:51,040
No!

17
00:00:52,260 --> 00:00:57,680
No!

18
00:00:57,680 --> 00:01:01,720
- No, no!
- Excuse me.

19
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:03,440
This...

20
00:01:03,440 --> 00:01:05,200
Oh, I'm sorry.

21
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:07,780
What is this?

22
00:01:14,560 --> 00:01:18,500
It's all your fault. If you didn't cause all that disturbance,

23
00:01:18,500 --> 00:01:20,400
I wouldn't have that kind of nightmare.

24
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:23,220
I already told you I'm sorry.  You still haven't let it go?

25
00:01:23,220 --> 00:01:26,760
They're coming back from their honeymoon tomorrow.

26
00:01:26,760 --> 00:01:28,680
What should I do?

27
00:01:28,680 --> 00:01:31,120
Should I take a couple of days off?

28
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:33,100
Why? You care that much?

29
00:01:33,100 --> 00:01:36,260
Of course!

30
00:01:36,260 --> 00:01:39,720
People are taking bets to see if  I'm going to resign or not.

31
00:01:39,720 --> 00:01:41,840
The people at your company really have a lot of time on their hands.

32
00:01:41,840 --> 00:01:45,880
That's what I say!  What did I do wrong? I'm a victim too!

33
00:01:45,880 --> 00:01:49,460
The person who should be consoled is me, don't you think?!

34
00:01:49,460 --> 00:01:52,110
Episode 2

35
00:01:54,420 --> 00:01:56,600
Thank you.

36
00:02:01,580 --> 00:02:03,180
Don't be worked up about this in the morning.

37
00:02:03,180 --> 00:02:05,740
Go to work and don't make it too obvious. You're good at acting tough.

38
00:02:05,740 --> 00:02:07,940
That's easier said than done.

39
00:02:07,940 --> 00:02:09,680
Excuse me!

40
00:02:16,140 --> 00:02:18,220
You left this there.

41
00:02:19,420 --> 00:02:22,940
But... don't you remember me?

42
00:02:25,740 --> 00:02:29,740
Won, I'll call you back later.

43
00:02:29,740 --> 00:02:31,500
Oh, okay.

44
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:34,760
Are you talking about me?

45
00:02:34,760 --> 00:02:37,620
Yes. I think I know you.

46
00:02:38,740 --> 00:02:43,040
What is this? Am I getting hit on right now?

47
00:02:43,040 --> 00:02:46,020
By this young and handsome guy?

48
00:02:46,020 --> 00:02:48,380
Wow, how could we meet at this kind of place?

49
00:02:48,380 --> 00:02:50,340
You really don't remember me?

50
00:02:51,720 --> 00:02:53,540
I don't know...

51
00:02:53,540 --> 00:02:55,480
I don't really remember...

52
00:02:55,480 --> 00:02:58,140
Oh, really?

53
00:02:58,140 --> 00:03:00,760
Thanks for this.

54
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:14,360
Timing and Subtitles brought by The Timeless Lovers @ Viki

55
00:03:22,140 --> 00:03:25,220
Those numbers are correct, Team Leader.

56
