00:43:22,390 --> 00:43:24,050
Hello?

514
00:43:24,990 --> 00:43:26,600
Hello?

515
00:43:28,280 --> 00:43:31,180
- That, that.
- Here.

516
00:43:35,940 --> 00:43:37,940
Oh, pepper!

517
00:43:37,940 --> 00:43:39,620
Pepper! Okay.

518
00:43:39,620 --> 00:43:41,460
This one.

519
00:43:41,460 --> 00:43:43,120
This.

520
00:43:50,200 --> 00:43:52,960
Madame Choi! This is really going overboard!

521
00:43:52,960 --> 00:43:58,440
If you really like him so much, why don't you do the grocery shopping yourself? Why would ask me to do the work?

522
00:43:58,440 --> 00:44:01,860
Okay, I got it. This is really the last time, okay?

523
00:44:01,860 --> 00:44:04,300
You're doing it now already.

524
00:44:04,300 --> 00:44:06,160
You are going to do it again.

525
00:44:06,160 --> 00:44:08,980
You know how sulky she can be.

526
00:44:08,980 --> 00:44:15,020
Figures. If you act out too, you'll probably be fighting everyday.

527
00:44:15,020 --> 00:44:19,740
Of course, my personality is good.

528
00:44:19,740 --> 00:44:22,140
That is why I've been seeing you for seventeen years.

529
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:25,960
What? I think you're misunderstanding something.

530
00:44:25,960 --> 00:44:28,040
I'm the one that's putting up with you.

531
00:44:28,040 --> 00:44:31,610
You are a very harsh person. It's just that people don't know it.

532
00:44:35,900 --> 00:44:40,440
You've been living in the same house but you still don't know Unni Mi Hyang's preferences?

533
00:44:40,440 --> 00:44:42,340
Ah, seriously.

534
00:44:42,340 --> 00:44:45,440
For Unni Mi Hyang,

535
00:44:45,440 --> 00:44:49,620
it's this. This.

536
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:02,700
Oh, Choi Won. How did you know that I like this?

537
00:45:05,100 --> 00:45:08,380
Since you guys are here, there is something you need to do for me.

538
00:45:09,520 --> 00:45:12,460
If you do this,

539
00:45:12,460 --> 00:45:15,880
does Mir or Milk, whatever his name is, even know you?

540
00:45:15,880 --> 00:45:17,840
Hey, so you didn't know?

541
00:45:17,840 --> 00:45:20,120
Mir loves the food I make for him.

542
00:45:20,120 --> 00:45:23,440
I heard that from the manager, that Mir would like it if I, as the fanclub president, came often.

543
00:45:23,440 --> 00:45:25,500
Wow, you believe that?

544
00:45:25,500 --> 00:45:28,240
It's all because the manager wants to eat it.

545
00:45:28,240 --> 00:45:31,200
Last time, it was pork rib hangover soup. Before that, it was cow blood soup.

546
00:45:31,200 --> 00:45:35,620
Now it's stir-fried chicken soup. Where do you see these foods as foods that idols like?

547
00:45:35,620 --> 00:45:37,960
I think I have to go confirm it personally.

548
00:45:37,960 --> 00:45:41,300
Unni.

549
00:45:43,280 --> 00:45:46,480
Here.

550
00:45:46,480 --> 00:45:49,140
Wow, it's so good.

551
00:45:49,140 --> 00:45:51,020
Right?

552
00:45:51,020 --> 00:45:54,660
If I was Mir, I would really marry you.

553
00:45:54,660 --> 00:45:57,740
He should hold on to you tightly when you are making such delicious food like this.

554
00:45:57,740 --> 00:46:00,380
Oh my, why are you like that?

555
00:46:00,380 --> 00:46:04,140
Oh, I'm embarrassed.

556
00:46:04,140 --> 00:46:07,740
Hey, do you know how large the age gap between her and that punk is?

557
00:46:07,740 --> 00:46:09,860
Hey, it isn't that big a difference.

558
00:46:09,860 --> 00:46:14,660
Twenty... why is age so important?

559
00:46:16,580 --> 00:46:20,740
But Unni... if Mir asks you out, would you really go out with him?

560
00:46:20,740 --> 00:46:26,180
Why do you keep being like that? I like it.

561
00:46:26,180 --> 00:46:29,820
What is there is to life? Is age such a big deal?

562
00:46:29,820 --> 00:46:31,500
Well,

563
00:46:35,230 --> 00:46:37,160
that's true.

564
00:46:48,200 --> 00:46:50,000
Grandmother, should I help you?

565
00:46:52,180 --> 00:46:54,620
The wheel on this thing is broken.

566
00:46:54,620 --> 00:46:56,980
Oh,

567
00:46:56,980 --> 00:46:59,500
you're right.

568
00:47:01,680 --> 00:47:04,520
Oh...

569
00:47:04,520 --> 00:47:07,460
It is probably heavy.

570
00:47:07,460 --> 00:47:09,560
It's alright.

571
00:47:13,760 --> 00:47:15,320
I'm sorry, what should I do?

572
00:47:15,320 --> 00:47:16,880
It's alright.

573
00:47:16,880 --> 00:47:20,960
This much is do-able. I'm strong.

574
00:47:33,080 --> 00:47:35,400
So Eun, I'll carry it.

575
00:47:35,400 --> 00:47:37,820
It's heavy though, Sunbae.

576
00:47:37,820 --> 00:47:38,960
Where do you have to go?

577
00:47:38,960 --> 00:47:40,660
Just to the front.

578
00:47:40,660 --> 00:47:41,560
Okay.

579
00:47:41,560 --> 00:47:43,520
Then I'll take your luggage for you, Sunbae.

580
00:47:43,520 --> 00:47:45,200
Okay.

581
00:47:52,040 --> 00:47:54,460
Where is your carry-on?

582
00:47:54,460 --> 00:47:56,340
Oh right.

583
00:48:29,060 --> 00:48:30,640
Excuse me.

584
00:48:30,640 --> 00:48:31,720
Yes?

585
00:48:31,720 --> 00:48:34,800
Do you have this in 245 cm?

586
00:48:37,040 --> 00:48:39,220
Hold on a second.

587
00:48:40,380 --> 00:48:42,380
Oh.This one too...

588
00:48:42,380 --> 00:48:44,140
Ah, yes.

589
00:49:00,800 --> 00:49:02,580
I'll do it.

590
00:49:34,400 --> 00:49:41,340
Timing and Subtitles brought by The Timeless Lovers @ Viki

591
00:49:59,600 --> 00:50:02,020
Why are you staring at me like that?

592
00:50:05,580 --> 00:50:07,380
I'm not.

593
00:50:17,460 --> 00:50:19,160
Here it is.

594
00:50:40,220 --> 00:50:43,080
You've worked hard.

595
00:50:57,180 --> 00:50:59,260
Put these on.

596
00:51:00,840 --> 00:51:03,260
Your feet hurt.

597
00:51:07,680 --> 00:51:09,080
Where did you get them?

598
00:51:09,080 --> 00:51:13,100
I borrowed them from the manager. I told them I'll give them back tomorrow.

599
00:51:15,000 --> 00:51:16,700
Hurry.

600
00:51:27,140 --> 00:51:28,900
Wow.

601
00:51:57,180 --> 00:52:02,500
It's no fun, right? Since you only keep doing on-site work at the department store.

602
00:52:02,500 --> 00:52:06,240
No. I learn from all the experience, anyway.

603
00:52:06,240 --> 00:52:11,480
If you really want to study shoes, the production business is more right for you.

604
00:52:11,480 --> 00:52:15,000
If you're interested, I'll talk to the department head.

605
00:52:16,240 --> 00:52:18,660
I like it now too.

606
00:52:18,660 --> 00:52:23,220
Thanks to Noona, I am learning a lot.

607
00:52:24,060 --> 00:52:27,260
Noo...na?

608
00:52:27,260 --> 00:52:32,940
We've left work. If we left work, you're not the team leader,

609
00:52:34,660 --> 00:52:36,960
and I'm not an intern either.

610
00:52:49,620 --> 00:52:54,420
I've arrived. That's... my house.

611
00:52:56,460 --> 00:52:58,240
Yes.

612
00:52:58,240 --> 00:52:59,560
My shoes.

613
00:52:59,560 --> 00:53:01,280
Ah.

614
00:53:07,360 --> 00:53:10,840
Go. I'm going in.

615
00:53:10,840 --> 00:53:12,380
Yes.

616
00:53:17,920 --> 00:53:22,140
Won. What are you doing there?

617
00:53:22,140 --> 00:53:25,220
I was throwing out the trash.

618
00:53:31,260 --> 00:53:34,300
Ah, this is the new intern at the company, Gi Seong Jae.

619
00:53:34,300 --> 00:53:36,640
I talked about him last time.

620
00:53:36,640 --> 00:53:39,760
Oh, that little boy...

621
00:53:44,100 --> 00:53:47,280
This is my friend, Choi Won.

622
00:53:48,760 --> 00:53:49,900
Hello.

623
00:53:49,900 --> 00:53:54,020
I've heard a lot about you, that you help Ha Na a lot.

624
00:53:54,020 --> 00:53:55,660
Well, I'm learning more.

625
00:53:55,660 --> 00:53:57,200
Yeah.

626
00:54:06,300 --> 00:54:07,520
I'll see you tomorrow.

627
00:54:07,520 --> 00:54:10,200
Yes. Then I'll be going now.

628
00:54:33,740 --> 00:54:36,260
- Call?
- Call.

629
00:54:38,800 --> 00:54:41,040
How is he?

630
00:54:41,040 --> 00:54:44,640
Well, like you said, he's like kids these days.

631
00:54:44,680 --> 00:54:47,120
Right?

632
00:54:47,150 --> 00:54:52,480
He's very bold. When we were coming home, he called me noona.

633
00:54:52,520 --> 00:54:57,650
Since we're not at work, he said I'm not the team leader and he's not the intern.

634
00:54:57,660 --> 00:54:59,520
Isn't it funny?

635
00:55:03,200 --> 00:55:05,030
What is it?

636
00:55:06,450 --> 00:55:08,320
Did you get shaken by that kid?

637
00:55:08,320 --> 00:55:10,750
No!

638
00:55:19,350 --> 00:55:21,110
I don't know either.

639
00:55:21,110 --> 00:55:22,870
Heol.

640
00:55:23,990 --> 00:55:31,000
What is it? So you thought of him as a man when he called you Noona?

641
00:55:31,020 --> 00:55:32,730
That's not it!

642
00:55:32,730 --> 00:55:35,990
He's good-looking, hard-working, and treats me well.

643
00:55:35,990 --> 00:55:38,680
You got shaken.

644
00:55:38,680 --> 00:55:42,290
Hey, how old am I to be shaken with just something like that?

645
00:55:42,290 --> 00:55:45,940
Then why didn't you do anything when he called you noona?

646
00:55:48,350 --> 00:55:50,030
You said you know how to separate love from work.

647
00:55:50,030 --> 00:55:52,150
You said what you call each other describes your relationship and all that—

648
00:55:52,150 --> 00:55:54,290
HEY!

649
00:55:55,410 --> 00:55:59,230
Okay. Then go with it, since it turned out this way.

650
00:55:59,230 --> 00:56:01,860
Do well and catch the young guy, get married next year,

651
00:56:01,860 --> 00:56:05,860
have triplets, and keep on going. Just keep going.

652
00:56:05,860 --> 00:56:10,730
Right, do I have to prepare $5,000? Can I pay you through my card by installment—

653
00:56:10,730 --> 00:56:12,740
Hey, come over here.

654
00:56:12,740 --> 00:56:14,590
By installment is not acceptable!

655
00:56:14,590 --> 00:56:16,910
- Just give it to me in a lump sum.
- Hey, let go.

656
00:56:16,910 --> 00:56:19,690
- Let go of me. Are you not letting go?
- I can't, I can't.

657
00:56:19,690 --> 00:56:23,400
- I'll give you $1000 each time. Hey, surrender, surrender!
- That won't work.

658
00:56:23,400 --> 00:56:26,080
- Ow, ow.
- Hey, hey.

659
00:56:27,870 --> 00:56:31,020
Please go to the factory and get all the samples for the fall /winter models.

660
00:56:31,020 --> 00:56:33,490
Check the list, and make sure nothing gets left behind.

661
00:56:33,490 --> 00:56:36,820
Alright, I'll be back.

662
00:56:41,620 --> 00:56:46,220
Yes, Manager. How much increased revenue do we have from the sale merchandise?

663
00:56:51,650 --> 00:56:55,920
Our schedule got cancelled? This is a miracle!

664
00:56:55,920 --> 00:56:58,740
You're right. This is the first time since I was a newbie.

665
00:56:58,740 --> 00:57:02,280
We can't spend a historical day like today doing nothing.

666
00:57:02,280 --> 00:57:04,100
How about a drink?

667
00:57:04,100 --> 00:57:06,580
No.

668
00:57:06,580 --> 00:57:09,460
Sunbae!

669
00:57:24,400 --> 00:57:26,970
Oh Ha Na, it's raining so do you want  spicy chicken feet?

670
00:57:26,970 --> 00:57:28,710
Thank you!

671
00:57:28,710 --> 00:57:30,860
Customer in the back, please come here.

672
00:57:30,860 --> 00:57:33,560
Thank you!

673
00:57:55,520 --> 00:57:57,880
Are you okay?

674
00:57:57,880 --> 00:58:00,080
I'm sorry.

675
00:58:20,870 --> 00:58:25,570
I'm on the way, so when I get in front of your office, I'll text you again.

676
00:58:47,280 --> 00:58:49,210
Are you getting off of work?

677
00:58:49,210 --> 00:58:52,220
Yes, Team Leader.

678
00:59:15,280 --> 00:59:17,200
You're here?

679
00:59:18,340 --> 00:59:19,720
Let's go.

680
00:59:19,720 --> 00:59:22,350
I'll go first.

681
01:00:25,310 --> 01:00:28,150
Oppa!

682
01:00:30,190 --> 01:00:35,360
♬  There is no reason to love you  ♬

683
01:00:37,000 --> 01:00:42,740
♬  But I didn't know that.  ♬

684
01:00:43,860 --> 01:00:50,780
♬  You, so blinding a  person ♬

685
01:00:50,780 --> 01:00:57,630
♬  were definitely there beside me.  ♬

686
01:00:57,630 --> 01:01:04,320
♬  Was it always warm  ♬

687
01:01:04,320 --> 01:01:10,860
♬  with you as the only one for me ♬

688
01:01:10,860 --> 01:01:14,740
♬  Is it okay to laugh about it? ♬

689
01:01:14,740 --> 01:01:18,360
♬  On the hard days past ♬

690
01:01:18,360 --> 01:01:22,370
♬  Because you were always there ♬

691
01:01:22,420 --> 01:01:24,350
Cham, cham, chan!

692
01:01:24,360 --> 01:01:28,630
♬  Even my heart didn't know how I felt ♬

693
01:01:28,700 --> 01:01:29,900
Hurry!

694
01:01:30,000 --> 01:01:31,500
Who's next? Hurry and get on!

695
01:01:31,530 --> 01:01:37,920
♬ Perhaps because you were always beside me ♬

696
01:01:37,930 --> 01:01:41,860
♬ From when it was ♬

697
01:01:41,860 --> 01:01:45,740
♬ Or how it started ♬

698
01:01:45,740 --> 01:01:48,270
♬ Neither you nor I were aware ♬

699
01:01:48,270 --> 01:01:51,830
Me? I'm going to the reading room.You?

700
01:01:51,830 --> 01:01:54,070
I'm going to the cathedral with Na Yeong.

701
01:01:54,090 --> 01:01:55,570
Oh.

702
01:01:55,570 --> 01:01:57,280
Work hard!

703
01:01:57,280 --> 01:01:59,190
Yeah, you too.

704
01:02:06,220 --> 01:02:12,960
♬  I always said it was not so  ♬

705
01:02:13,030 --> 01:02:18,490
♬  My heart was foolish.   ♬

706
01:02:19,820 --> 01:02:26,690
♬  Were we comfortable  ♬
♬  enough to be silent ♬

707
01:02:26,730 --> 01:02:30,460
♬  and to pretend we didn't know? ♬

708
01:02:30,460 --> 01:02:32,280
The Time I've Loved You

709
01:02:32,280 --> 01:02:33,890
Aren't you going all-out these days?

710
01:02:33,890 --> 01:02:36,890
- I heard you had that kind of relationship with your intern.
- Really?

711
01:02:36,890 --> 01:02:40,010
I'm going on a business trip. You're coming with me, so get ready.

712
01:02:40,010 --> 01:02:41,650
Even today, fighting! I love you.

713
01:02:41,650 --> 01:02:44,680
She seduced an intern eight years younger than her, and now it's like this.

714
01:02:44,730 --> 01:02:47,020
Kang Na Yeong! How long has it been?

715
01:02:47,020 --> 01:02:48,990
- Na Yeong?
- Yeah, the girl who used to like you.

716
01:02:48,990 --> 01:02:52,500
- This won't do.
- When was it when you said to keep my eyes on Hyung Won?
- You were together?

717
01:02:52,500 --> 01:02:54,480
Oppa, you'll be my black knight, right?

718
01:02:54,480 --> 01:02:57,690
She's very different from an ordinary girl. If he doesn't get swayed by that girl, he's not even a man.

719
01:02:57,690 --> 01:03:01,440
What, they've been together until now?
